<br> Born Free, Live Free, Die Free. <br>
<br> Bona na Croin <br>(Neither Collar Nor Crown)</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub76.ezboard.com/ugwion.showPublicProfile?language=EN>gwion</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><b><font color=yellow>RA Council Member</font><br><b><font color=blue>Administrator</span><br>  Posts: 1330<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(12/12/01 12:12:02 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_mad.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Very Aggravated</span><hr size=1> I got all the newest gamer stuff I could when I bought my PC -- two years ago <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :lol --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/laugh.gif ALT=":lol"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   It looked fine to me, but apparently it's practically a dinosaur.<br>
<br>
Or it was.  In anticipation of Luclin, I upgraded from my beloved Voodoo3 to a GEForce 2 (~$100) and went from 128 MB of RAM to 512 (~$75 and I didn't look for a deal, either).<br>
<br>
Now Luclin runs fine, except for some lag in parts of the cat city--but that's no worse than Kunark was when it came out.<br>
<br>
Installing the new stuff wasn't very hard.  I was intimidated about opening up the tower, so I brought Ag over to help, but I think I could have done it myself.  The RAM slots were pretty obvious, and the old video card popped right out.  <br>
<br>
I was up and running in less than an hour -- of course I had to fiddle about with my stupid software decoder for the DVD, but that's another story <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :lol --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/laugh.gif ALT=":lol"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  (How was I supposed to know about DTS sound encoding? Sheesh!)<br>
<br>
I know how you feel about constantly having to buy new stuff; it ticks me off too.  You get a new 'puter and it's great, but a month later it's &quot;slow&quot;.  I don't have a car because it ticks me off that cars start to devalue the minute you drive them off the lot -- and this is a good investment because...? <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :lol --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/laugh.gif ALT=":lol"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <br>
<br>
So I live without a car (ah, freedom), but I can't live without a 'puter, so I put up with the pressure to buy new stuff.  I give in only when I absolutely must -- and Luclin was one of those times. <p><font color=green><font size=3>Gwion Llewellyn</font><br><font color=white><font size=2>Level, um, 42<br>"It ain't a party until something gets broken!"</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub76.ezboard.com/uemerest.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Emerest</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><b>RA Officer<b></span><br>  Posts: 339<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(12/12/01 12:38:11 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_mad.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Very Aggravated</span><hr size=1> The thing about the car is that you can use it for years with only minor adjustments, providing you take reasonably good care of it.<br>
<br>
If I want to drive to a new location, go exploring in some place I've never been before, as long as there is a road, I can go (actually, I've got one of those cars which can go even if there is no road, as long as theere's no really deep water  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> ).  I don't need to get new tires, or a new engine, or a better steering wheel.  I just get in and go.<br>
<br>
Apparently, this is not the case with my computer.  I want to go somewhere new, so I have to pamper it, buy it new toys and handle it with extreme care (can't shock the poor old thing).  Either that, or chuck it and find a younger one!  Either way, it's expensive. And in the case of Verant, I have to do this just to go to all the places I used to go to yesterday!  Very frustrating.<br>
<br>
And we won't even talk about having to be technically oriented (I'm not, as several of you can attest to -- thanks Am and Lego for all your help!), just to get things up and running.  I don't have to be an auto mechanic to drive my car.<br>
<br>
Sheesh.  Good luck, E!  I hope things work out for you soon. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub76.ezboard.com/uelryyc.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Elryyc</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><b>RA Member</span><br>  Posts: 169<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(12/12/01 5:55:28 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_mad.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Very Aggravated</span><hr size=1> Well, being a pc tech by trade, I know how easy it would be to upgrade.... if not for one thing. Lack of upgradeability !<br>
<br>
Never again will I buy a Presario or similar PC. 3 expansion slots - all full. Integrated audio chipset, poorly supported now. Memory ? Try only 2 DIMM banks, both full. Processor ?? Oh, but then you have to be able to change some settings on the motherboard for the cyles, etc - and there aren't any settings available on this proprietary board. (I'm a Compaq Certified tech now - should have known sooner !)<br>
<br>
However, an interesting development occurred today that has some promise. October 1st I was involved in an accident when some old feller ran a red and totalled me out. I am fine now, but had to go to ER and have XRays and do some therapy for a while. Well, today the insurance company called me and offered me a very modest amount in addition to covering my expenses and reimbursing me for lost wages. It's not much, but it might be enough to get components to build a new system. I'll keep you posted.<br>
